>
  <h2>Why is Online Safety Important?</h2>
  <p>
    The internet is an amazing place to learn and have fun — but just like crossing the road, you need to follow some important safety rules to stay protected!
  </p>

  <h2>🚨 The Golden Rules</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>🏠 <strong>Never share personal info</strong> — Don't give out your home address, phone number, school name, or full name to strangers online.</li>
    <li>🔑 <strong>Use strong passwords</strong> — Mix letters, numbers, and symbols. Never share your password with anyone except a parent or guardian.</li>
    <li>🤔 <strong>Think before you click</strong> — Don't click strange links or download unknown files. They might contain viruses!</li>
    <li>👨‍👩‍👧 <strong>Tell a trusted adult</strong> — If anything online makes you feel scared, uncomfortable, or confused, always tell a parent or teacher right away.</li>
    <li>🎭 <strong>Not everyone is who they say they are</strong> — Online strangers may pretend to be someone they're not.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What is a Strong Password?</h2>
  <p>A strong password should be:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>At least <strong>8 characters</strong> long.</li>
    <li>A mix of <strong>UPPERCASE and lowercase letters</strong>.</li>
    <li>Include <strong>numbers</strong> (like 3, 7, 9).</li>
    <li>Include <strong>special characters</strong> (like @, !, #).</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    ✅ Good password: <code>Blue5ky!Jump</code><br/>
    ❌ Bad password: <code>password123</code>
  </blockquote>

